The paper discusses the negative effects of optimization systems on populations and environments, and proposes Protective Optimization Technologies as a solution. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category, as it deals with algorithmic decision-making and recommender systems. Additionally, the paper touches on issues of fairness and bias, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) categories. The proposal of novel frameworks and solutions also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories.
